{
  "message": "security: untrack MCP config files containing bearer tokens\n\nfactory.mcp.json, codex.mcp.json, cursor.mcp.json, and gemini.mcp.json\nwere still tracked despite *.mcp.json being in .gitignore (added before\nthe rule). These files contained local bearer tokens that should never\nbe in version control.\n\n- Remove all *.mcp.json from git index (git rm --cached)\n- Add factory.mcp.json.template with placeholder token\n- Local copies preserved for existing users\n\nNote: the historical token (a6e3aa9b...) from commit 5d737c6 remains in\ngit history. Since this is a localhost-only bearer token for the Agent\nMail HTTP server (127.0.0.1:8765), the exposure risk is limited to\nlocal-network scenarios. A full history rewrite (git filter-repo) would\nbreak all existing clones and is not warranted for a local-only token.\nUsers who deployed with the default token should rotate it.\n\nCloses #33\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
